        "Shapes fall into three broad categories, each with distinct communicative properties. Geometric shapes — circles, squares, rectangles, triangles, polygons — are defined by mathematical precision and regularity. They convey order, stability, efficiency, and modernity. Organic shapes are irregular, free-flowing forms with curved or unpredictable contours, typically associated with nature, biology, and human expression. They convey warmth, approachability, and natural authenticity. Abstract shapes simplify or stylize recognizable subjects into essential forms, as seen in icons, pictograms, and logos.",
