        "Color is arguably the most emotionally powerful element of design. Before a viewer reads a single word, color has already communicated mood, category, urgency, and brand identity. A red banner signals danger, sale, or passion. A blue interface suggests trust, calm, and technology. A green label implies nature, health, or environmental responsibility. These associations are deeply embedded — some through biology (we are hardwired to notice red as an alerting color), some through cultural convention (white symbolizes purity in Western cultures but mourning in many East Asian traditions), and some through learned brand associations (Coca-Cola red, Tiffany blue, UPS brown).",
