        "The concept of visual voice — the distinctive personality that emerges from a design's element choices — is the ultimate expression of integration. Just as a writer's voice emerges from vocabulary, syntax, and tone, a designer's visual voice emerges from the specific combination of line quality, shape vocabulary, color palette, typographic choices, spatial relationships, and texture treatments. A design with a strong visual voice feels authored and intentional; one without feels generic and interchangeable. Developing a consistent visual voice across a project or brand is the mark of design maturity.",
